###################################################################################
example1
####################################################################################
Description: RPA calculation without local field effects of the macroscopic
             dielectric tensor projected on the (1 0 0) q-direction, for bulk
             silicon.
Output:
   -epsilon.nlf.RPA contains in xml format the full (3*3) macroscopic
    dielectric tensor
   -repsilon.nlf.RPA contains the real part of the macroscopic
    dielectric tensor projected on (1 0 0) q direction as a function of energy (Ry)
   -oas.nlf.RPA contains format the simulated optical absorption spectra
    on (1 0 0) q direction as a function of energy (Ry)
   -eels.nlf.RPA contains format the electron energy loss spectra for q->0
    in the (1 0 0) direction
Suggestions:
   -to include local field effects just change in the spectra.x input
    the following: local_field_effects="T"
Note:
   the inclusion of local field effects in homogeneous system has almost a negligible
   effect on the spectra.

In the /reference directory the user can find the textual main output of the example1
run. The calculations have been performed with a pc and the g95 fortran compiler.
####################################################################################
